# Agent Protocols — environment variables example
#
# Copy this file to `.env` at the project root and fill in the values your
# deployment needs. The orchestration scripts authenticate to GitHub via
# `gh auth login` by default (token read from the OS keychain), so this
# file is OPTIONAL for the headline install path — most adopters do not
# need any of the entries below.

# --- Notifications (optional) -----------------------------------------------
# Webhook URL the structured notifier posts wave/epic/story digests to.
# Leave unset to disable notifications. Supports Slack-compatible incoming
# webhooks.
NOTIFICATION_WEBHOOK_URL=

# --- Projects V2 fallback (only needed if `gh auth login` did not grant `project` scope) ---
# The headline install path uses `gh auth login` and reads tokens from the
# OS keychain — no PAT is required for Issues, Labels, PRs, or branches.
# Set GITHUB_TOKEN (or GH_TOKEN) only if you use Projects V2 integration
# AND your `gh auth login` did not request the `project` scope. The
# Projects V2 GraphQL shim falls back to this token to set up the Project,
# its status field, and views.
#
# To grant the scope to `gh` instead (preferred), re-run:
#   gh auth refresh -h github.com -s project
#
# GITHUB_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
# GH_TOKEN=ghp_xxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxxx
